	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I added a simple metasprite editor to MapEd Pro. If anyone is interested, I could post an update.<br /><br />Animation formats:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">1: &#91;FRAME, TIME&#93;&#91;...&#93;&#91;CTRL_CODE&#93;<br />2: &#91;COUNT&#93;&#91;FRAME, TIME&#93;&#91;...&#93;<br />3: &#91;START&#93;&#91;LENGTH&#93;&#91;TIME&#93;<br /></div><br />Frame formats:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">1: &#91;COUNT&#93;&#91;Y, T, A, X&#93;&#91;...&#93;<br />2: &#91;COUNT&#93;&#91;A&#93;&#91;Y, T, X&#93;&#91;...&#93;<br /></div><br /><br />Coordinates can be signed or unsigned. It doesn't cover all cases, but most of the commercial games I've seen used something similar.<br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: 65%; line-height: normal">I've been testing other things that were added to the program, so I haven't posted a new version in a while.</span>

		
